[thinking] **Considering Java class access**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the structure of Java classes. If I create a separate top-level public class, I realize that Java allows only one public class per file, but I can have package-private top-level classes. I'm unsure if a dynamically loaded class needs to be public. I wonder if `getConstructor` really only returns public constructors for public classes. If the class is package-private, the constructor wouldn't be accessible, which leads me to think about the necessity of top-level public classes in dedicated files.
[thinking] 
